<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
        <title>PCCurrency</title>
        <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:wght@100&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css"></link>
    </head>
    <body>
        <form action="/logout" class="linkbtn">
            <button>Log out</button>
        </form>
        <form action="/place" class="linkbtn">
            <button>Place</button>
        </form>
        <form action="/manageAccount" class="linkbtn">
            <button>Manage</button>
        </form>
        <form action="/api" class="linkbtn">
            <button>API</button>
        </form>

        <h1>Welcome, <nodejs-embed>username</nodejs-embed></h1>
        <b>Your balance is</b>: <nodejs-embed>currencyAmount</nodejs-embed> PC
        <form action="/hallOfTransactions" class="linkbtn">
            <button>Hall of Transactions</button>
        </form>
        <form action="/give" class="linkbtn">
            <button>Create a transaction</button>
        </form> <br>
        <b>On Place</b>, you have put <nodejs-embed>dailyPixAmount</nodejs-embed> pixels out of 1024. If you place more than that, you can still place pixels, but you won't earn any money. This limit resets <label class="datify"><nodejs-embed>isologon</nodejs-embed></label>. <br>
        <form action="/difficulty" class="linkbtn">
            <button><b>Mining difficulty</b></button>
        </form> [<a href="/mining">download miner</a>] is set to <nodejs-embed>currentDifficulty</nodejs-embed>.
        <script src="/datify.js"></script>
    </body>
</html>